{
  "video_id": "rx1l51qxGbQ",
  "title": "What Staring At A Screen All Day Is Doing To Your Brain And Body | The Human Body",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 500.0,
      "end_time": 2560.0,
      "text": "It's 11 PM."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2560.0,
      "end_time": 4830.0,
      "text": "You should be asleep, but you're watching"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 4830.0,
      "end_time": 8390.0,
      "text": "a video on your phone and tomorrow you'll wake up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 8390.0,
      "end_time": 9930.0,
      "text": "and go to work, where you'll stare"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 9930.0,
      "end_time": 12900.0,
      "text": "at a computer for eight hours."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 12900.0,
      "end_time": 16540.0,
      "text": "When you get home, you might even watch a movie on TV."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 16540.0,
      "end_time": 19410.0,
      "text": "So if you're anything like the average American adult,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 19410.0,
      "end_time": 22250.0,
      "text": "you spend more than seven hours a day"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 22250.0,
      "end_time": 25180.0,
      "text": "staring at digital screens."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 25180.0,
      "end_time": 27520.0,
      "text": "So what's all this screen time actually doing"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 27520.0,
      "end_time": 28893.0,
      "text": "to your body and brain?"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 32910.0,
      "end_time": 36180.0,
      "text": "Surprise, surprise, humans did not evolve to stare"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 36180.0,
      "end_time": 39360.0,
      "text": "at bright electronic screens all day"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 39360.0,
      "end_time": 42769.0,
      "text": "so our eyes are suffering the consequences."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 42770.0,
      "end_time": 46440.0,
      "text": "An estimated 58% of people who work on computers"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 46440.0,
      "end_time": 50419.0,
      "text": "experience what's called computer vision syndrome."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 50420.0,
      "end_time": 53240.0,
      "text": "It's a series of symptoms that include eye strain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 53240.0,
      "end_time": 56960.0,
      "text": "blurred vision, headaches, and neck and back pain."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 56960.0,
      "end_time": 60100.0,
      "text": "And in the longterm this amount of screen time"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 60100.0,
      "end_time": 62480.0,
      "text": "could be damaging our vision permanently."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 62480.0,
      "end_time": 66470.0,
      "text": "Since 1971, cases of nearsightedness in the US"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 66470.0,
      "end_time": 68740.0,
      "text": "have nearly doubled, which some scientists"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 68740.0,
      "end_time": 71440.0,
      "text": "partly link to increased screen time."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 71440.0,
      "end_time": 74240.0,
      "text": "And in Asia today, nearly 90%"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 74240.0,
      "end_time": 76929.0,
      "text": "of teens and adults are nearsighted."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 76930.0,
      "end_time": 79100.0,
      "text": "But it's not just the brightness of our screens"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 79100.0,
      "end_time": 81320.0,
      "text": "that affect us, it's also the color."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 81320.0,
      "end_time": 85290.0,
      "text": "Screens emit a mix of red, green, and blue light."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 85300.0,
      "end_time": 86840.0,
      "text": "Similar colors to sunlight."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 86840.0,
      "end_time": 90800.0,
      "text": "And over a millennia it was blue wavelengths in sunlight"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 90800.0,
      "end_time": 92940.0,
      "text": "that helped us keep our circadian rhythms"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 92940.0,
      "end_time": 94710.0,
      "text": "in sync with our environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 94710.0,
      "end_time": 97149.0,
      "text": "But since our circadian rhythms are more sensitive"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 97150.0,
      "end_time": 99130.0,
      "text": "to blue light than any others, a problem occurs"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 99130.0,
      "end_time": 102500.0,
      "text": "when we use our screens at night."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 102500.0,
      "end_time": 103670.0,
      "text": "Typically when the sun sets"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 103670.0,
      "end_time": 106400.0,
      "text": "we produce the hormone melatonin."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 106400.0,
      "end_time": 108810.0,
      "text": "This hormone regulates our circadian rhythms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 108810.0,
      "end_time": 111520.0,
      "text": "helping us feel tired and fall asleep."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 111520.0,
      "end_time": 113420.0,
      "text": "But many studies have found that blue light"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 113420.0,
      "end_time": 116200.0,
      "text": "from screens can disrupt this process."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 116200.0,
      "end_time": 118440.0,
      "text": "For example, in one small study,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 118440.0,
      "end_time": 121250.0,
      "text": "participants who spent four hours reading e-books"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 121250.0,
      "end_time": 125570.0,
      "text": "before bed for five nights, produced 55% less melatonin"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 125570.0,
      "end_time": 128250.0,
      "text": "than participants that read print books."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 128250.0,
      "end_time": 130860.0,
      "text": "What's more, the e-book readers reported"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 130860.00000000001,
      "end_time": 133380.0,
      "text": "that they were more alert before bed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 133380.0,
      "end_time": 137359.0,
      "text": "took longer to fall asleep and reach restorative REM state,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 137360.0,
      "end_time": 140100.0,
      "text": "and were more tired the next morning."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 140100.0,
      "end_time": 142430.0,
      "text": "But perhaps the most concerning changes"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 142430.0,
      "end_time": 144470.0,
      "text": "we're starting to see from all this screen time"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 144470.0,
      "end_time": 146650.0,
      "text": "is in kid's brains."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 146650.0,
      "end_time": 149640.0,
      "text": "An ongoing study, supported by the NIH"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 149640.0,
      "end_time": 152000.0,
      "text": "has found that some preteens who clocked"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 152000.0,
      "end_time": 153930.0,
      "text": "over seven hours a day on screens"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 153930.0,
      "end_time": 157800.0,
      "text": "had differences in a part of their brain called the cortex."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 157800.0,
      "end_time": 159370.0,
      "text": "That is the region responsible"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 159370.0,
      "end_time": 162960.0,
      "text": "for processing information from our five senses."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 162960.0,
      "end_time": 166380.0,
      "text": "Usually the cortex gets thinner as we mature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 166380.0,
      "end_time": 170180.0,
      "text": "but these kids had thinner cortexes earlier than other kids"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 170180.0,
      "end_time": 172920.0,
      "text": "who spent less time on screens."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 172920.0,
      "end_time": 174929.0,
      "text": "Scientists aren't sure what this could mean"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 174930.0,
      "end_time": 178100.0,
      "text": "for how the kids learn and behave later in life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 178100.0,
      "end_time": 180859.0,
      "text": "but the same data also showed that kids who spent"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 180860.0,
      "end_time": 182730.0,
      "text": "more than two hours a day on screens"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 182730.0,
      "end_time": 186880.0,
      "text": "scored lower in thinking and in language skill tests."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 186880.0,
      "end_time": 189410.0,
      "text": "To be clear, the NIH data can't confirm"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 189410.0,
      "end_time": 193630.0,
      "text": "if more time spent staring at screens causes these effects,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 193630.0,
      "end_time": 195650.0,
      "text": "but they'll have a better idea of any links"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 195650.0,
      "end_time": 197320.0,
      "text": "as they continue to follow and study"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 197320.0,
      "end_time": 199709.0,
      "text": "these kids over the next decade."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 199710.0,
      "end_time": 201670.0,
      "text": "It's no doubt that screens have changed"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 201670.0,
      "end_time": 205250.0,
      "text": "the way we communicate, but only time will tell"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 205250.0,
      "end_time": 208763.0,
      "text": "what other changes are on the horizon for human kind."
    }
  ]
}